form (<i>Hreodbeorht</i>), which was supplanted by the Norman name. Two dukes of Normandy in the 11th century bore the name: the father of  William the Conqueror  (sometimes identified with the legendary Robert the Devil), and his eldest son. It was borne also by three kings of Scotland, notably  Robert the Bruce  (  1274–1329 ), who freed Scotland from English domination. The altered short form <i>Bob</i> is very common, but <i>Hob</i> and <i>Dob</i>, which were common in the Middle Ages and gave rise to surnames, are extinct.  See also  Rupert ."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Robert DeAquillon was born in 1180, in Withyham, Sussex, England, United Kingdom. He had at least 1 son and 2 daughters."},"et":{"1180–":"1180–Surnud","1175–Female":"1175–Surnud","1200–Male":"1200–Surnud","1336–Female":"1336–Surnud","1180–Male":"1180–Surnud","1336":"1336","1200":"1200","1175":"1175","1180":"1180","Withyham, Sussex, England":"Withyham, Sussex, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1180–":"1180–Kuollut","1175–Female":"1175–Kuollut","1200–Male":"1200–Kuollut","1336–Female":"1336–Kuollut","1180–Male":"1180–Kuollut","1336":"1336","1200":"1200","1175":"1175","1180":"1180","Withyham, Sussex, England":"Withyham, Sussex, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"1180–":"1180–Décédé","1175–Female":"1175–Décédée","1200–Male":"1200–Décédé","1336–Female":"1336–Décédée","1180–Male":"1180–Décédé","1336":"1336","1200":"1200","1175":"1175","1180":"1180","Withyham, Sussex, England":"Withyham, Sussex, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","lifeSummary":"Robert DeAquillon est né en 1180, à Withyham, Sussex, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni. Il a eu au moins 1 fils et 2 filles."},"de":{"1180–":"1180–Verstorben","1175–Female":"1175–Verstorben","1200–Male":"1200–Verstorben","1336–Female":"1336–Verstorben","1180–Male":"1180–Verstorben","1336":"1336","1200":"1200","1175":"1175","1180":"1180","Withyham, Sussex, England":"Withyham, Sussex, England, United Kingdom","lifeSummary":"Robert DeAquillon wurde 1180 in Withyham, Su